,{"source":"recJhMBucEbOC6FyV","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec6l4Iardk75VmJS","ref":"Joel.1.1","text":"The word of the LORD that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.","year":-800},{"id":"recRVq3N3CWrjzMyx","ref":"Joel.1.2","text":"Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?","year":-800},{"id":"recI48xbfBQSMq3MU","ref":"Joel.1.3","text":"Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.","year":-800},{"id":"recsNLqRhR6ND3lti","ref":"Joel.1.4","text":"That which the palmerworm hath left hath the locust eaten; and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten; and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpiller eaten.","year":-800},{"id":"recDzgZNsnX6rgARW","ref":"Joel.1.5","text":"Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine; for it is cut off from your mouth.","year":-800},{"id":"recfgNaRhF7teRMRG","ref":"Joel.1.6","text":"For a nation is come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the cheek teeth of a great lion.","year":-800}]}
